# How to Work with CSV Files

## Introduction

A CSV (Comma-Separated Values) file is a text file in a specific format that allows you to save data as a table. In the workplace, translators often encounter CSV files. It's essential to know how to handle them. They can be opened and edited in Excel. Below, I describe how to deal with CSV files using an example file available at:

[Sample CSV File](https://people.sc.fsu.edu/~jburkardt/data/csv/csv.html)

## Steps to Work with CSV Files

### 1. Downloading the Sample CSV File

   a. Copy the URL: [https://people.sc.fsu.edu/~jburkardt/data/csv/csv.html](https://people.sc.fsu.edu/~jburkardt/data/csv/csv.html)
   
   b. Open a web browser.
   
   c. Paste the URL into the address bar and press Enter.
   
   d. Locate and download the CSV file.

### 2. Opening the CSV File in Excel

   a. Launch Microsoft Excel.
   
   b. Choose "Open" from the menu.
   
   c. Locate and select the downloaded CSV file.
   
   d. Click "Open".

### 3. Editing Data in the CSV File

   a. Once the file is opened in Excel, you can edit its contents.
   
   b. Add, remove, or modify values in individual cells.

### 4. Saving Changes to the CSV File

   a. After editing, select "Save" or "Save As" from the menu.
   
   b. Choose the CSV file format.
   
   c. Save the changes.

## Learning Outcomes

Upon completing these steps, you have achieved the following objectives:

- Ability to open CSV files in Excel.
- Understanding how to edit the content of a CSV file.
- Learning to save changes made to a CSV file.

Additionally, you have gained the skill of working with files having different extensions than traditional ones.
